er level and stuff, id never go in lottos for stuff I couldn`t use, id never go in for things I already had, and then I started to notice a few things like that the people that did go in and stuff were making cash by selling the things I gave up for the good of the group, or to help an individual. My mage was in 27 lottos for an SMR, which was won by warriors and sometimes unluckily in 50 50 lottos with one other wizard type, and still never won anything. It seems that in certain cases it pays to be greedy. I hate it, I will never go in for an item that someone can use, but you never really no for sure if they are going to use it or just hawk it, and if thats the case, then I should be going in, but I still am hesitant.<br>
<br>
The other thing I notice is certain people dont care about me like I do about them. If I was in a group and had a wicked 2h slash item, and another one dropped but the warrior I was with had a crap one, I would suggest he get it if no one else could use it; others might disagree and say they could &quot;trade it&quot; for something to better their character, but at least for me this undermines the thrill a bit, but recently it seems that the more ya hoard, the more youll end up with.<br>
<br>
Oh well was bored at work, just figured I`d share some thoughts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/umunchausen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Munchausen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#939393>(10/28/00 3:22:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   greed</span><hr size=1> The point is it dont matter what other people do in the game bro.  Play the game the way you feel it should be played and dont pay attention to others.  One day you are gonna be sitting at level 60 (or close to it) have all the loot you desire and then realize what eq is about - PEOPLE (not saying YOU dont know this already).  I can tell you that there is no loot in the game that will matter when your best friend says he is leaving because EQ is'nt fun anymore.  If you can make the game better for someone else do it.<br>
<br>
