58 Shaman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uwysteriaplushfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wysteria Plushfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://nmcs.com/images/sisters.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#939393>(10/28/00 4:47:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Greed.</span><hr size=1> Case in point, a guild mate today was in Karnor's, the lone warrior in the group when the rare Cobalt boots dropped.  He was the only warrior and he expected to get the boots.  Imagine his disappointment when the group leader allowed an enchanter to also roll for the boots... and the enchanter won them.  For his twink.<br>
<br>
Just remember folks, what goes around comes around.  Or is it the other way?  I can't remember.  Generally in Kunark it is the custom to give the loot to the person who has a character in the group that can use it (not a twink).  This is because loot tends to be more random and there's stuff there for everyone.  You don't have to camp one particular mob for your class armor (for the most part).  In the old world, like Lower Guk, loot would only drop off of one particular mob.  Therefore, if you wanted to have a balanced group, you'd pretty much have to allow everyone to random for it.  Otherwise, clerics, warriors and so on would have no interest in camping the spawn that drops the SMR (for instance).  Does the way loot drops in the old world suck?  Sure!  It means that someone might lose a whole bunch of times for something they could use, while someone else gets it.  But, the alternative is to have a bunch of robe-wearers grouping by themselves to get the prize.  Or the other alternative is to gather a few friends that will see to it you get the robe!  <br>
<br>
Also, it points out the importance of making sure EVERYONE is clear on the looting rules before some important loot drops.  At least, if you don't like the rules you can find a group with rules that are more inline with what you think is fair.  It's up to the group leader to set the rules and keep everyone informed as they join the group.  Making up the loot protocol on the fly is just asking for trouble.<br>
<br>
Wysteria <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udoofyrainbowfloater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Doofy Rainbowfloater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#939393>(10/28/00 9:02:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Greed.</span><hr size=1> class specific loot givin to an enchanter over a warrior is just wrong. I believe the same for the SMR. But that's the way it's been done in Guk on tunare for ages. One good thing though, is the SMR is only going for about 6k now adays, so if you save up for a few days, well, depending on your level and how easily you can get items, just save up. it's alot better than pulling your hair out waiting for spawn.<br>
